This paper is about iterative algorithms for compressed sensing, which is a subfield of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the dynamics of these algorithms, which involves statistical analysis and machine learning techniques (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses generating functional analysis, which is a mathematical tool commonly used in numerical analysis and computational physics (cs.NA). The paper also discusses the large system limit, which is a topic in statistical physics and complexity theory (cs.SI). Finally, the paper is related to signal processing and image analysis, which falls under the subfield of multimedia (cs.MM).
